users
The users category refers to the table in the database schema designed to store information about registered users, including identifiers and personal details.

products
The products category contains the table structure for information about available products in the database, detailing fields like name, price, and supplier.

orders
The orders category outlines the structure of storing order information, linking users to the products they purchase, including payment and shipping details.

user_id
user_id is a unique identifier assigned to users in the database.<SEP>user_id is the primary key for the users table, uniquely identifying each registered user and automatically incrementing for new entries.

username
username is a non-nullable field in the users table, representing the user's chosen name, which must be unique.<SEP>username is a unique name chosen by each user for identification purposes.

email
email is a crucial field in the users table, required to be unique and non-null, representing the user's electronic communication address.<SEP>email is the electronic mail address associated with each user.

password
password is a secured string that users create to protect their accounts.<SEP>password is used for user authentication, stored as an encrypted value in the users table and must be non-null.

product_id
product_id is the primary key for the products table, uniquely identifying each product and automatically incrementing for new entries.

product_name
product_name is a required field in the products table, representing the name of the product and must not be null.

price
price is a critical non-nullable field in the products table indicating the cost of the product.

quantity_in_stock
quantity_in_stock is a non-nullable field in the products table that reflects the available stock of the product.

order_id
order_id is the primary key for the orders table, serving as a unique identifier for each order and automatically incrementing.

order_date
order_date captures the timestamp when an order is created, with a default value set to the current time.

user_id (orders)
user_id in the orders table acts as a foreign key linking to the users table to associate each order with its respective user.

product_id (orders)
product_id in the orders table serves as a foreign key linking to the products table to associate each order with the purchased product.

full_name
full_name is an optional field that allows users to record their complete name in the users table.<SEP>full_name refers to the complete name of the user as recorded in the database.

address
address is an optional field in the users table that stores the user's physical address.<SEP>address is the physical location where the user resides.

phone_number
phone_number is an optional field in the users table that stores the user's contact number.<SEP>phone_number is the contact number provided by each user.

created_at
created_at indicates the date and time when the user account was established.<SEP>created_at is a timestamp indicating when the user's record was created, automatically set to current time.

description
description is an optional field that provides detailed information about the product in the products table.

category (products)
category is an optional field that identifies the product category in the products table.

warranty_period
warranty_period is an optional field that records the warranty duration for the product.

rating
rating is an optional field that reflects the average score of the product based on user reviews.

quantity (orders)
quantity is a non-nullable field in the orders table that indicates the number of products ordered.

shipping_address
shipping_address is an optional field that records where the order will be delivered.

billing_address
billing_address is an optional field that captures where the invoice will be sent.

status
status is a field in the orders table that indicates the current state of the order (e.g., pending, shipped).

payment_method
payment_method is an optional field indicating how the order was paid for (e.g., PayPal, Credit Card).

total_amount
total_amount is an optional field that specifies the total cost of the order, including any applied taxes and fees.
